'''Adam Conover''' (born March 2)<ref>https://mobile.twitter.com/AdamRuins/status/969693356199727104</ref> is an American comedian, writer, voice actor, and television host. He is the creator and [[Television presenter|host]] of the half-hour [[truTV]] show ''[[Adam Ruins Everything]]'', which is based on the [[CollegeHumor]] series of the same name.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-tv-picks-colbert-frontline-bomber-adam-ruins-everything-tcm-20150925-column.html | title=TV Picks: 'Late Show,' 'My Brother's Bomber,' 'Adam Ruins Everything' | work=Los Angeles Times | date=26 September 2015 | accessdate=11 October 2015 | author=Lloyd, Robert}}</ref> He is also the host of the American version of ''[[The Crystal Maze]]'' on Nickelodeon.
== Early life == [[File:Olde english comedy.png|thumb|left|Members of the sketch comedy group Olde English. From left to right: Ben Popik, [[Raphael Bob-Waksberg]], David Segal, Caleb Bark, and Adam Conover]] Adam Conover was born in [[Smithtown, New York]],<ref name=tbr>{{cite web | url=http://tbrnewsmedia.com/north-shore-native-ready-to-ruin-trutv/|title=North Shore native ready to ‘ruin’ truTV | work=The Times Beacon Record | date=24 September 2015 | accessdate=19 October 2015 | author=Barkley, Giselle}}</ref> and grew up in [[Wading River, New York|Wading River]].<ref name=newsday>{{cite web | url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/adam-ruins-everything-li-s-adam-conover-creates-witty-trutv-humor-series-1.10886646 | title='Adam Ruins Everything': LI's Adam Conover creates witty truTV humor series | work=Newsday | date=28 September 2015 | accessdate=11 October 2015 | author=Lovece, Frank}}</ref> His parents are [[David O. Conover]], a marine biologist,<ref name=FastCompany>{{cite web|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/3051462/spoiler-alert-adam-conover-hilariously-dispels-all-your-beliefs-to-teach-you-a-lesson|title=Spoiler Alert: Adam Conover Hilariously Dispels All Your Beliefs To Teach You a Lesson|last=Champagne|first=Christine|date=29 September 2015|website=Fast Company|accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref> and Margaret Conover (née Howard), a [[botanist]].<ref name=tbr/><ref name=newsday/><ref name=FastCompany/> He also has a younger sister, Emily, who holds a PhD in [[particle physicist|particle physics]] and is a science reporter, which has led him to describe himself as "the only member of the family without a [[Ph.D.]]"<ref>{{cite web | url=https://reason.com/archives/2016/02/21/what-you-think-you-know-is-wro|title=What You Think You Know Is Wrong | work=Reason | date=21 February 2016 | accessdate=11 March 2016|author=Weissmueller, Zach}}</ref> In 2000, he graduated from [[Shoreham-Wading River High School]], where he became interested in the performing arts.<ref name=riverhead>{{cite web | url=http://riverheadnewsreview.timesreview.com/2015/10/68608/watch-as-this-shoreham-wading-river-grad-ruins-everything/ | title=Watch as this Shoreham-Wading River grad ‘Ruins Everything’ | work=Riverhead News-Review | date=8 October 2015 | accessdate=11 October 2015 | author=Smith, Nicole}}</ref> He then attended [[Bard College]], where, in 2002, he became an active member of the [[sketch comedy]] group [[Olde English (sketch comedy)|Olde English]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/25/arts/television/adam-conover-turns-a-skeptical-eye-to-the-presidential-campaign.html?_r=0 |title=Adam Conover Turns a Skeptical Eye to the Presidential Campaign |last=Genzlinger |first=Neil |website=The New York Times |publication-date=24 October 2016}}</ref> In 2004,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bard.edu/news/events/event/?eid=116844&date=1347408000|title=The Exquisite Corpse Project|website=Bard College|access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref> he earned a [[bachelor's degree]] in philosophy from Bard College.<ref name=newsday/>
== Career == In 2012, Conover began working as a sketch [[comedy]] writer and performer for the comedy website and YouTube channel [[CollegeHumor]], where he eventually created the web series that would go on to become ''[[Adam Ruins Everything]]'' on [[TruTV]].<ref name=newsday/><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/show/adam_does_emnot_em_ruin_everythingmdashfact | title=Adam Does Not Ruin Everything—FACT!| work=Skeptical Inquirer | date=29 August 2018 | accessdate=29 August 2018 |first= Gerbic |last= Susan |authorlink=Susan Gerbic }}</ref> The first episode of the truTV show, which aims to reveal untold truths and to dispel common misconceptions,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/spotlight/adam-conover-adam-ruins-everything-trutv-emmy-sam-reich-collegehumor-1202456092/|title=TruTV’s ‘Adam Ruins Everything’ Promotes Facts in the Age of Fakery|last=Hendrickson|first=Paula|date=2017-06-07|work=Variety|access-date=2017-10-09|language=en-US}}</ref> premiered on September 29, 2015. Conover has said his character in the show is a comedic interpretation of the person he worries he once was and/or is. As he told the ''[[New York Observer]]'', "It’s the reaction I’ve gotten my whole life: that I learn something and try to tell people in conversation, but when I tell them, they are annoyed."<ref>{{cite web | url=http://observer.com/2015/09/adam-ruins-everything-creator-adam-conover-on-trutvs-secretly-informative-comedy/ | title=‘Adam Ruins Everything’ Creator Adam Conover on Making Difficult Truths Into Comedy | work=The Observer | date=29 September 2015 | accessdate=21 August 2016 | author=Grant, Drew}}</ref>
In March 2016, he was asked to speak at a [[marketing]] [[Convention (meeting)|conference]] on the subject of millennials; the talk he gave was entitled "Millennials Don't Exist".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://mic.com/articles/138525/comedian-nails-the-one-simple-thing-adults-can-do-to-connect-with-young-people#.Fj39Ky6aB | title=This Comedian Just Obliterated All Stereotypes About Millennials in One Presentation | work=Mic | date=21 March 2016 | accessdate=25 May 2016 | author=Singer, Sarah}}</ref> In 2018, Conover was the headliner of the first night of the annual [[CSICon]] conference for skeptics.<ref name="Conover">{{cite journal |last1=Fidalgo |first1=Paul |title=Parasites and modern mind control |journal=Skeptical Inquirer |date=2019 |volume=43 |issue=2 |page=15}}</ref> On August 17, 2018, Conover was a guest on ''[[Real Time with Bill Maher]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/real-time-with-bill-maher/episode-24-season-16/preet-bharara-adam-conover-jennifer-granholm-charlie-sykes-jonathan-swan/192190|title=Real Time with Bill Maher {{!}} TV Guide|website=TVGuide.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-13}}</ref> On April 17, 2019, Conover was a guest on ''[[The Joe Rogan Experience]]''.
He has voiced several characters in the [[Netflix]] animated series ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'', including [[List of BoJack Horseman characters#A Ryan Seacrest Type|A Ryan Seacrest-Type]], one of the [[List of BoJack Horseman characters#Paparazzi Birds|Paparazzi Birds]], and [[List of BoJack Horseman characters#Minor characters|Bradley Hitler-Smith]].<ref name=newsday/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/adamconover/status/859476492379541504 |title=Yep! I also play Bradley Hitler-Smith, aka Ethan from Horsin' Around!|last=Conover |first=Adam |date=2017-05-02 |website=@adamconover |language=en |access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> In 2019, he voiced the character of "Big_Hairy_Stallion_69" on the Netflix series ''[[Tuca and Bertie]]'', and created the new [[Earwolf]] podcast ''Factually!''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/05/231643/tuca-bertie-character-voices-cast-season-1#slide-16 |title=Adam Conover Is The Voice Of Big_Hairy_Stallion69 (Aka Joel) |date=2019-05-03 |website=Refinery29 |language=en |access-date=2019-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adamconover.net/introducing-my-new-podcast-factually/|title=Introducing My New Podcast, Factually!|date=2019-05-24|website=Adam Conover: Official Site. Tour dates, Podcasts, Blog|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref>
Since 2020 Adam Conover is also the host of the Nickelodeon version of the family game show [[The Crystal Maze|''The Crystal Maze.'']]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/the-crystal-maze-names-adam-conover-host-nickelodeon-family-game-show-1202802945/|title=‘The Crystal Maze’ Taps Adam Conover As Host Of New Nickelodeon Family Game Show|last=Haring|first=Bruce|last2=Haring|first2=Bruce|date=2019-12-09|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>
== Personal life == Conover was once a roommate of ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' creator [[Raphael Bob-Waksberg]] in [[New York City]], who also introduced him to his girlfriend, illustrator [[Lisa Hanawalt]].<ref name="thecut.com">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecut.com/2018/09/lisa-hanawalt-of-bojack-horseman-talks-to-heather-havrilesky.html|title=Don’t Look BoJack’s Gifted Horse-Lady in the Mouth|first=Heather|last=Havrilesky|date=Sep 7, 2018|website=The Cut|accessdate=May 27, 2019}}</ref>
Conover quit drinking in early 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dykes, Brett Michael|url=https://uproxx.com/tv/adam-conover-adam-ruins-everything-interview/|title=Adam Conover Of 'Adam Ruins Everything' Is Loving RSS Feeds Again|date=April 23, 2018|publisher=[[Uproxx]]}}</ref>
